 Incident Management 
o Case Management team should be automatically assigned based on 
the availability of the Surveyor, Adjustor, Case Management also 
keeping in mind the Surveyor field office covers the area where 
vehicle is for repairs. 
o Surveyor should be able to submit their assessment online  via 
website or app and once the surveyor assignment is submitted the 
adjustor should be notified. 
o Adjustor should be able to view the claim, supporting document, 
assessment report online and should be able to adjudicate the claim 
based on policy coverage. 
Promotion Case Study - Assessment for Senior Staff Engineer 
o In case Surveyor or Adjustor is not available for claims processing 
the case manager should be able to delegate the claim processing 
to other Surveyor or Adjustor. 
o Case Manager should be able to view the complete details of the 
case and make adjustment to claims which can override the 
Adjustor and surveyor. 
o Auditor can look at all the details pertaining to the claims and any 
processing.
• Internal Users Reporting 
o Internal user should be able to login to the portal. 
o Only Authorized Case Managers should be able to generate reports 
with respect to the claims they have received. 
o Regional Manager should be able to see the details with respect to 
claims received in their region with details like 
▪ Claims Processing Time 
▪ Claims amount paid out 
▪ Number of claims with respect to geography. 
o Top management should be able to generate reports based on how 
each region is processing with respect to claims, which region more 
claims are being received, which region has higher claims amount 
paid out. 